Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @Irish pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Break the mince up with a #spoon{} as it cooks. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve and deseed the @bell pepper{1}. Slice into thin strips.

Add the pepper and onion to the pork and fry for ~{4-5%mins}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} and fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @tomato paste{1%tin}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{to taste}.

Lower the heat to medium and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Place the @naan{2} on a lined #baking tray{} and distribute the pork evenly between them, leaving a 1cm border around the edge as the crust.

Sprinkle over the @grated cheese{50%g} and pop into the oven.

Bake until the cheese is melted, ~{4-6%mins}.

Just before serving, toss the @salad leaves{40%g} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and half the @balsamic glaze{2%sachets}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the loaded naans between #plates{}.

Top with a drizzle of remaining balsamic glaze.

Spoon over the @Ballymaloe tomato relish{1%pot}.

Scatter a little salad on the naans and serve the remaining salad alongside.